CHANGELOG
=========

2026-01-27
----------
- Added Vale prose linting configuration (.vale.ini)
- Added custom vocabulary for kernel.org technical terms
- Fixed prose style issues in access.rst, ksmap.rst, linuxdev.rst, lore.rst,
  gitolite/index.rst
- Updated ksmap.rst: replaced COVID-19 specific note with general guidance on
  video conference keysigning
- Updated wiki.rst: documented that wiki hosting has been discontinued and
  users should use ReadTheDocs-style documentation sites
- Updated gitolite/track_set.rst: documented that the track subcommand has
  been retired since all backend Linux repositories now share objects
- Updated linuxdev.rst: added application template for linux.dev account
  requests
- Added email-hosting.rst: recommended email hosting options for maintainers
- Added korgalore.rst: documentation for korgalore mailing list import tool
- Updated linuxdev.rst: added korgalore as recommended alternative for
  high-volume mailing list content
- Added cross-references between related documents:
  - email-hosting, korgalore, linuxdev, mail (email topics)
  - accounts, ksmap, pgpkeys (PGP/keysigning topics)
  - access, fido2 (SSH access topics)
  - lore, korgalore (archive access topics)
- Reorganized lore.rst: now describes the service with links to public-inbox
  and korgalore; archive collection instructions moved to lore-archives.rst
- Added lore-lei.rst: quick start guide for using lei with lore.kernel.org
- Added kernel.org logo
